results.name: Number of nonisomorphic ways a loop can cross three roads meeting in a Y n times (orbits under symmetry group of order 6).
comment: There is no constraint on touching any particular sector.
The Mercedes-Benz problem: closed meanders crossing a Y.
example: With three crossings the loop must cut each road exactly once, so a(3) = 1.
With 4 crossings the loop can cut one road 4 times (one possibility), or two roads twice each (one possibility), so a(4) = 2.
xref: Cf. A078104 (total number of solutions), A077460 and A005315 (loop crossing one road).
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_ and _Jon Wild_, Dec 05 2002
